023-10-12-at-9.38.56-1024x442.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20always%20the%20risk%20of%20over-analysing%20these%20narratives%20of%20solidarity.%20Yet%2C%20for%20those%20interested%20in%20the%20sharp%20turns%20of%20modern%20Indian%20politics%2C%20there%20is%20some%20value%20in%20unpacking%20the%20subtext%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20embrace%20of%20Israel%20as%20it%20reveals%20a%20few%20more%20things%20about%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20Hindu%20nationalist%20project%2C%20its%20aspirations%20and%20ideological%20directions%20through%20the%20decades%2C%20than%20about%20Zionism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20key%20themes%20become%20conspicuous%20in%20the%20rhetoric%20contained%20in%20the%20above%20posts%20%E2%80%93%20transnational%20solidarity%20built%20on%20cultural%20nationalism%2C%20identification%20of%20a%20common%20enemy%2C%20and%20shared%20values%20of%20hyper-militarism.%20All%20three%20aspects%20play%20on%20each%20other.%20But%2C%20to%20really%20deconstruct%20the%20unprecedented%20wave%20of%20India-Israel%20transnational%20solidarity%2C%20we%20need%20to%20go%20deeper%20into%20the%20shared%20imaginaries%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20and%20Zionist%20projects.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECommon%20cultural-nationalist%20dreams%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindutva%20movement%E2%80%99s%20fascination%20with%20the%20Zionist%20project%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20early%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century.%20Both%20VD%20Savarkar%20and%20MS%20Golwalkar%20%E2%80%93%20the%20two%20stalwarts%20of%20modern%20Hindutva%20thought%20%E2%80%93%20had%20expressed%20sympathy%20and%20admiration%20for%20Jews%20for%20remaining%20committed%20to%20their%20cultural%20practices%20despite%20the%20monumental%20persecution%20that%20they%20faced.%20But%2C%20not%20just%20that%2C%20they%20looked%20up%20to%20the%20Zionists%20for%20giving%20a%20tangible%20shape%20to%20their%20nationalist%20aspirations%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20Jewish%20state.%20A%20great%20deal%20of%20this%20cross-cultural%20affinity%20arose%20from%20a%20sense%20of%20nationalist%20and%20racial%20insecurity%20inherent%20in%20early%20Hindutva%20thought%2C%20which%20ultimately%20generated%20the%20need%20to%20establish%20a%20Hindu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(nation)%20as%20a%20corrective%20measure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Satadru%20Sen%2C%20who%20teaches%20South%20Asian%20history%20at%20the%20City%20University%20of%20New%20York%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F00856401.2015.1077924%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2015%20article%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESouth%20Asia%3A%20Journal%20of%20South%20Asian%20Studies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Golwalkar%20saw%20in%20%E2%80%9CJews%20and%20Hindus%20a%20shared%20political%20problem%20that%20stemmed%20from%20a%20clash%20between%20the%20reality%20of%20race%20and%20the%20failure%20of%20nationhood.%E2%80%9D%20In%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBunch%20of%20Thoughts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Golwalkar%20refers%20to%20Jews%20(and%20Parsis)%20living%20in%20India%20as%20%E2%80%9Cguests%E2%80%9D%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20Muslims%20and%20Christians%20who%20were%20%E2%80%9Cinvaders%E2%80%9D.%20This%20reflects%20Hindutva%E2%80%99s%20acceptance%20of%20Jews%20as%20non-threatening%20members%20of%20the%20Hindu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20who%20could%20co-exist%20peacefully.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESavarkar%20too%20framed%20Hindus%20and%20Jews%2C%20as%20Sen%20observes%2C%20in%20the%20language%20of%20%E2%80%9Cracial%20units%E2%80%9D.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20reframing%20of%20Hinduism%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Crace%E2%80%9D%20has%20today%20become%20a%20core%20driving%20force%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20ethnonationalist%20project.%20When%20combined%20with%20other%20unifying%20markers%2C%20such%20as%20language%20and%20culture%2C%20both%20the%20%E2%80%9CHindu%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9CJew%E2%80%9D%20could%20be%20refashioned%20as%20ethnic%20super-identities%20that%20can%20then%20subsume%2C%20if%20not%20displace%2C%20other%20social%20identities%20(like%20Dalits%20and%20Muslims).%20Add%20to%20this%20transformative%20mix%20a%20modern%20nation-state%20with%20a%20strong%20military%2C%20and%20you%20end%20up%20with%20a%20formidable%20ethno-state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20intelligentsia%2C%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20is%20a%20striking%20manifestation%20of%20this%20complex%20arc%20that%20begins%20at%20cultural%20assertion%20and%20culminates%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20ethnic%20%E2%80%98homeland%E2%80%99%20protected%20by%20military%20force%20and%20exclusivist%20laws.%20Yet%2C%20without%20specific%20territorial%20limits%2C%20an%20ethno-state%20remains%20incomplete%20and%20ineffective.%20So%2C%20an%20essential%20aspect%20of%20this%20process%20is%20territorial%20reclamation%20and%20in%20turn%2C%20the%20production%20of%20a%20bounded%20national%20space%20through%20the%20physical%20displacement%20of%20other%20%E2%80%9Cdispensable%E2%80%9D%20identities%3B%20the%20creation%20of%20what%20Polish-Jewish%20scholar%2C%20Zygmunt%20Bauman%2C%20has%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgardening%20state%E2%80%9D.%20Both%20the%20older%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20and%20their%20modern%20political%20agents%20recognise%20this%20imperative%20with%20much%20sincerity%2C%20and%20see%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20ready-made%20and%20fairly%20successful%20model%20for%20replication.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F12%2Fhindutva-rss-sangh-parivar-bjp-pti.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shredded%20social%20cohesion%20is%20the%20first%20symptom%20of%20fragility.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-203955%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHindutva%20groups.%20Representative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20irredentist%20%E2%80%9Cmodel%E2%80%9D%20is%20partly%20driven%20by%20a%20colonising%20impulse.%20As%20Jewish-Israeli%20scholar%2C%20Ilan%20Pappe%2C%20has%20astutely%20observed%20in%20his%20writings%2C%20early%20Zionist%20policy%20was%20inherently%20premised%20on%20establishing%20full%20control%20over%20the%20native%20Palestinian%20population%20through%20a%20meticulously-designed%20military-governorate%20regime%2C%20which%20has%20continued%20in%20nearly%20the%20same%20form%20till%20today.%20This%20architecture%20of%20control%20by%20brute%20force%20and%20legal%20diktat%20was%20a%20means%20to%20achieve%20a%20specific%20end%20%E2%80%93%20Judaizing%20Arab%20Palestine.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20modern%20Hindutva%20project%20seeks%20to%20Hinduize%2C%20using%20an%20equal%20mix%20of%20hard%20power%20and%20socio-legal%20tools%2C%20specific%20regions%20that%20lie%20outside%20of%20the%20Hindu%20cultural%20orbit.%20Of%20them%2C%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%20is%20the%20most%20prominent.%20While%20scholars%20like%20Nitasha%20Kaul%20have%20rightly%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgjia.georgetown.edu%2F2022%2F06%2F17%2Findia-israel-and-geopolitical-imaginaries-of-cooperation-and-oppression%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecautioned%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20against%20drawing%20direct%20comparisons%20between%20Kashmir%20and%20Palestine%20because%20of%20their%20varying%20political%20contexts%2C%20one%20cannot%20ignore%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20modern%20Hindutva%20elite%20itself%20tends%20to%20analogise%20both.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20for%20example%20the%20remarks%20made%20in%20November%202019%20by%20then%20Indian%20consul%20general%20in%20New%20York%20(currently%20Joint%20Secretary%2C%20Europe-West%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs)%2C%20Sandeep%20Chakraborty%2C%20at%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findian-consul-general-in-us-suggests-israel-model-for-kashmiri-pandits-return-kicks-up-row%2F327302%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprivate%20event%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20hosted%20by%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%20expats%20in%20the%20city.%20Talking%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20controversy%20around%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%20Chakraborty%20argued%20that%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20would%20be%20able%20to%20return%20to%20their%20homeland%20%E2%80%9Cin%20his%20lifetime%E2%80%9D%20just%20like%20the%20Israeli%20people%20were%20able%20to%20return%20to%20theirs.%20Without%20mincing%20words%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20already%20have%20a%20model%20in%20the%20world%2C%20I%20do%20not%20know%20why%20do%20not%20follow%20it.%20It%20has%20happened%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20If%20the%20Israeli%20people%20can%20do%20it%2C%20we%20can%20also%20do%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Chakraborty%20might%20have%2C%20inadvertently%20or%20otherwise%2C%20revealed%20a%20core%20objective%20of%20modern%20Hindutva%20statecraft%3A%20to%20replicate%20an%20Israeli-style%20settler-annexation%20model%20to%20undo%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwrongs%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20past%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20was%20the%20first%20major%20step%20towards%20achieving%20that%20goal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20a%20more%20recent%20example.%20In%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnishikant_dubey%2Fstatus%2F1710997899633704963%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epost%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20made%20on%20X%20on%20October%208%20in%20light%20of%20the%20ongoing%20clashes%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20Nishikant%20Dubey%2C%20a%20BJP%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20from%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Godda%20constituency%2C%20quoted%20a%20post%20by%20senior%20Congress%20MP%2C%20Jairam%20Ramesh%2C%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%20aspirations%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%E2%80%9D.%20Posting%20a%20picture%20of%20former%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20with%20the%20former%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Liberation%20Front%20(JKLF)%20chief%2C%20Yasin%20Malik%2C%20he%20implied%20that%20the%20Congress%20party%20has%20engaged%20in%20dialogue%20with%20elements%20that%20once%20violently%20evicted%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20from%20Kashmir%20and%20now%20want%20to%20chase%20Israel%20away%20from%20Tel%20Aviv.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22hi%5C%22%3E%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%B9%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%88%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%89%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%97%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B8%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9F%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%98%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%2C%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%87%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%89%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%87%E0%A5%A4%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%AD%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%89%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%97%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B8%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%8F%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%89%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AB%E0%A4%BC%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%B8%2C%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%95%2C%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B2%2CJKLF%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A5%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BF%E0%A