ltimedia%20journalist%20and%20an%20international%20development%20professional%2C%20seeking%20the%20release%20of%20illegally%20detained%20Rohingya%20refugees%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20states%20that%20international%20refugee%20law%20prohibits%20states%20from%20treating%20refugees%20and%20asylum%20seekers%20on%20the%20same%20footing%20as%20economic%20migrants.%20Despite%20this%2C%20the%20petition%20has%20alleged%20Rohingya%20detained%20for%20being%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20immigrants%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20held%20beyond%20their%20sentences%20or%20the%20maximum%20period%20of%20detention%20of%20foreign%20nationals%20as%20per%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20internal%20policy.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20cites%20the%202011%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20standard%20operating%20procedure%20to%20deal%20with%20foreign%20nationals%20who%20claim%20to%20be%20refugees%20as%20stating%20that%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20cases%20in%20which%20diplomatic%20channels%20do%20not%20yield%20concrete%20results%20within%20a%20period%20of%20six%20months%2C%20the%20foreign%20national%2C%20who%20is%20not%20considered%20fit%20for%20grant%20of%20LTV%20(Long%20Term%20Visa)%2C%20will%20be%20released%20from%20detention%20centre%20subject%20to%20collection%20of%20biometric%20details%2C%20with%20conditions%20of%20local%20surety%2C%20good%20behaviour%20and%20monthly%20police%20reporting%20as%20an%20interim%20measure%20till%20issuance%20of%20travel%20documents%20and%20deportation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20alleges%20that%20this%20guideline%20was%20not%20adhered%20to%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20Rohingya%20refugees%20and%20the%202019%20SOP%20has%20also%20done%20away%20with%20this%20provision%20of%20release%20from%20detention%20when%20deportation%20is%20not%20possible%20or%20taking%20an%20unreasonable%20amount%20of%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20their%20refugee%20status%2C%20the%20detention%20of%20Rohingya%20refugees%20is%20done%20under%20the%20Foreigners%20Act%2C%201946%2C%20which%20regulates%20immigration%2C%20the%20petition%20alleges.%20The%20Act%20provides%20for%20unchecked%20executive%20powers%20against%20foreigners%20and%20contains%20no%20special%20provisions%20for%20statutory%20exceptions%20for%20vulnerable%20populations%20like%20asylum%20seekers%20and%20refugees.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20absence%20of%20special%20protections%20for%20refugees%20in%20the%20Act%20has%20been%20used%20by%20the%20government%20to%20penalise%20refugees%20for%20lack%20of%20documentation%20like%20passports%20and%20visas%2C%20the%20petition%20has%20alleged.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20despite%20UNHCR%20recognition%2C%20registered%20Rohingya%20refugees%20in%20India%20are%20still%20at%20risk%20of%20administrative%20detention%20criminal%20imprisonment%20and%20deportation%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20claims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20sources%20its%20data%20from%20a%20UNHCR%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freporting.unhcr.org%2Findia-factsheet-4211%5C%22%3Efactsheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20dated%20November%202022%2C%20according%20to%20which%20312%20Rohingya%20refugees%20remain%20in%20immigration%20detention%2C%20263%20in%20a%20holding%20centre%20in%20Jammu%20and%2022%20at%20a%20welfare%20centre%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petitioner%20has%20submitted%20that%20based%20on%20interviews%20conducted%20with%20family%20members%20of%20detainees%2C%20Rohingya%20community%20leaders%20and%20lawyers%2C%20the%20numbers%20far%20exceed%20312.%20The%20petition%20claims%20that%20the%20approximate%20number%20of%20Rohingya%20refugees%20detained%20across%20India%20is%20above%20500%2C%20with%20almost%2050%25%20of%20them%20women%20and%20children%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20detained%20with%20their%20mothers%2Fpartners%20in%20detention%2C%20where%20they%20have%20no%20access%20to%20education.%20Older%20children%20are%20forcibly%20separated%20from%20their%20parents%20and%20kept%20in%20juvenile%20detention%20or%20homes%2C%20the%20petition%20has%20alleged.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20rarely%20get%20an%20opportunity%20to%20see%20their%20parents%20and%20spend%20years%20without%20any%20interaction%20with%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20has%20given%20graphic%20details%20of%20living%20conditions%20in%20detention%20centres%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Jammu%2C%20Assam%2C%20West%20Bengal%20and%20other%20jails%20across%20the%20country%2C%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20Chennai%2C%20Kochi%20and%20in%20states%20like%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Bihar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEstimates%20of%20the%20number%20of%20Rohingya%20refugees%20detained%20in%20India%20are%20complicated%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20clarity%20on%20what%20constitutes%20detention.%20The%20petition%20says%20what%20Indian%20authorities%20call%20%E2%80%9Cholding%20centres%E2%80%9D%20act%20effectively%20as%20detention%20centres.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.refugeesinternational.org%2Freports-briefs%2Fshadow-of-refuge-rohingya-refugees-in-india%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520November%25202022%252C%2520UNHCR%2520reported%2Cfor%2520detention%2520are%2520often%2520arbitrary.%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20co-authored%20by%20Daniel%20Sullivan%20and%20the%20petitioner%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Estates%20specific%20reasons%20for%20detention%20are%20often%20arbitrary.%C2%A0%20In%20one%20case%20currently%20before%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%2C%20a%20Rohingya%20woman%20describes%20being%20called%20by%20her%20local%20Rohingya%20leader%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20to%20a%20remote%20location%20to%20fill%20out%20some%20paperwork.%20Upon%20arrival%2C%20she%20was%20detained%20by%20the%20police%20and%20has%20been%20in%20detention%20ever%20since.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F01171400%2Fjail-prison.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F01171400%2Fjail-prison.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F01171400%2Fjail-prison-300x192.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F01171400%2Fjail-prison-1024x655.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-525972%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Tum%20Hufner%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20refugees%20interviewed%20for%20the%20report%20mentioned%20that%20police%20often%20use%20local%20leaders%20as%20informers%20or%20have%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangement%20of%20not%20detaining%20them%20if%20they%20can%20assist%20in%20getting%20other%20Rohingya%20detained.%C2%A0%20As%20one%20camp%20leader%20in%20Hyderabad%20told%20the%20team%2C%20local%20police%20pressured%20him%20to%20report%20who%20visits%20the%20settlement%20and%20threatened%20him%20with%20detention%20if%20he%20did%20not.%20If%20a%20new%20refugee%20is%20reported%20within%20a%20locality%2C%20they%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20detention.%20This%20leads%20to%20refugees%20in%20need%20of%20services%2C%20particularly%20new%20arrivals%2C%20staying%20in%20hiding%20unable%20to%20access%20hospitals%20or%20report%20crimes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20interviewee%20who%20had%20been%20detained%20for%20several%20months%20reported%20that%20people%20were%20held%20in%20rooms%20so%20tightly%20packed%20that%20detainees%20needed%20to%20take%20turns%20lying%20down%20to%20sleep.%20Other%20former%20detainees%20said%20the%20food%20given%20to%20them%20was%20watery%20and%20full%20of%20dirt%20and%20dead%20insects.%20Most%20previously%20detained%20refugees%20complained%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20sunlight%20in%20the%20holding%20detention%20area.%20These%20living%20conditions%20have%20raised%20the%20question%20of%20the%20right%20to%20live%20with%20dignity%2C%20guaranteed%20by%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution%20to%20all%20%E2%80%93%20including%20foreigners.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20writ%20petition%2C%20filed%20under%20Article%2032%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20seeks%20a%20writ%20of%20mandamus%20directing%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20to%20release%20Rohingya%20refugees%20who%20have%20been%20illegally%20and%20arbitrarily%20detained%20in%20jails%20and%20detention%20centres%20across%20the%20country%2C%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20their%20right%20to%20life%20and%20equality%20before%20law%20under%20Article%2021%20and%2014%20respectively.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Rohingya%20are%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2Femergencies%2Frohingya-crisis%5C%22%3Eethnic%20minority%3C%2Fa%3E%20originating%20from%20the%20Rakhine%20state%20in%20Myanmar.%20They%20have%20been%20described%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20persecuted%20ethnic%20minority.%20They%20have%20a%20history%20of%20statelessness%20since%201980%2C%20primarily%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%201982%20Citizenship%20Law%20enacted%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20which%20effectively%20stripped%20them%20of%20their%20citizenship.%20Escalated%20genocidal%20attacks%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Myanmar%20military%20in%20August%202017%20caused%20more%20than%207%2C70%2C000%20Rohingya%20to%20flee%20the%20country.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%202020%2C%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20(ICJ)%20gave%20a%20landmark%20judgment%20of%20grave%20significance%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20ethnic%20atrocities%20against%20the%20Rohingya%20community%20in%20Myanmar.%C2%A0%20The%20ICJ%20found%20that%20the%20Rohingya%20community%20in%20Myanmar%20had%20suffered%20genocide%20and%20ordered%20the%20government%20in%20Myanmar%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F01%2F23%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fmyanmar-rohingya-genocide.html%5C%22%3Erestrain%20its%20military%20forces%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20continuing%20with%20the%20oppression.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20submits%20that%20India%20has%20an%20obligation%20to%20prevent%20genocide.%C2%A0%20India%20had%20in%201948%20approved%20the%20Convention%20on%20the%20Prevention%20and%20Punishment%20of%20the%20Crime%20of%20Genocide%20which%20established%20%E2%80%98genocide%E2%80%99%20as%20an%20international%20crime%2C%20which%20signatory%20nations%20%E2%80%9Cundertake%20to%20prevent%20and%20punish%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20India%2C%20along%20with%20Panama%20and%20Canada%2C%20was%20the%20force%20behind%20the%20adoption%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20on%20December%209%2C%201948.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20not%20being%20a%20party%20to%20the%201951%20Convention%20on%20the%20Status%20of%20Refugees%2C%20India%20continues%20to%20host%20a%20large%20population%20of%20refugees%20and%20passed%20domestic%20laws%20on%20the%20right%20to%20life%20that%20apply%20to%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20also%20served%20on%20UNHCR%E2%80%99s%20executive%20committee%20since%201995%20and%20supported%20the%202018%20Global%20Compact%20on%20Refugees%2C%20a%20non-binding%20framework%20described%20by%20the%20UN%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20strengthen%20the%20international%20response%20to%20large%20movements%20of%20refugees%20and%20protracted%20refugee%20situations%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20alleges%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20denies%20exit%20permissions%20to%20those%20Rohingya%20who%20opt%20to%20resettle%20in%20other%20countries%20such%20as%20Canada%20and%20the%20US%20after%20obtaining%20visas%20from%20them.%20The%20government%20allows%20UNHCR%20mandate%20refugees%20to%20apply%20for%20visas.%20Refugees%20and%20asylum%20seekers%20have%20also%20been%20provided%20access%20to%20basic%20government%20services%20such%20as%20healthcare%20and%20education%20as%20well%20as%20to%20law%20enforcement%20and%20justice%20systems.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEstimates%20of%20the%20number%20of%20Rohingya%20living%20in%20India%20vary%20widely.%20The%20last%20public%20estimators%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20in%202017%20put%20the%20number%20at%2040%2C000.%20The%20Rohingya%20population%20in%20India%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20those%20who%20arrived%20following%20earlier%20periods%20of%20persecution%20and%20those%20who%20have%20arrived%20more%20recently%20from%20the%20camps%20in%20Bangladesh.%20According%20to%20the%20UNHCR%20factsheet%20dated%20November%202022%2C%2029%2C052%20Rohingya%20are%20registered%20with%20the%20UNHCR%20as%20of%20November%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInternational%20refugee%20law%20regards%20the%20asylum%20seeker%20as%20a%20presumptive%20refugee.%20A%20bonafide%20asylum%20seeker%20is%20to%20be%20given%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt%20and%20afforded%20all%20the%20rights%20of%20a%20refugee%20until%20their%20refugee%20claim%20is%20conclusively%20rejected%20by%20a%20competent%20authority.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20claims%20that%20many%20Rohingya%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20access%20UNHCR%20refugee%20cards%20yet.%C2%A0%20Some%20have%20been%20detained%20while%20on%20their%20way%20from%20other%20states%20to%20Delhi%20to%20approach%20the%20UNHCR%20and%20some%20have%20even%20been%20detained%20from%20outside%20the%20UNHCR%20office%2C%20the%20petition%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERohingya%20are%20recognised%20as%20refugees%2C%20and%20it%20is%20an%20established%20principle%20of%20international%20refugee%20law%20that%20they%20should%20not%20be%20returned%20or%20expelled%20to%20a%20state%20where%20they%20fear%20for%20their%20life%20and%20safety%2C%20the%20petition%20avers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697029962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F01175949%2FR3.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsc-seeks-centres-response-to-petition-seeking-release-of-illegally-detained-rohingya-refugees%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20admitted%20the%20petition%20filed%20by%20Priyali%20Sur%2C%20an%20independent%20multimedia%20journalist%2C%20on%20Tuesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsc-seeks-centres-response-to-petition-seeking-release-of-illegally-detained-rohingya-refugees%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CAG%20Officers'%20Transfers%3A%20Opposition%20Accuses%20Modi%20Government%20of%20'Intimidation'%2C%20'Corruption'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06163312%2FCAG-building-II.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Opposition%20parties%20have%20accused%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20of%20corruption%20after%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fofficers-cag-reports-ayushman-bharat-bharatmala-transferred%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20has%20transferred%20officers%2C%20including%20three%20who%20were%20coincidentally%20involved%20with%20and%20in%20charge%20of%20two%20audit%20reports%20that%20highlighted%20graft%20in%20the%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20Scheme%20and%20cost%20irregularities%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20Dwarka%20Expressway.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Congress%20MP%20and%20general%20secretary%20in-charge%20of%20communications%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1711978766837457183%5C%22%3Eaccused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintimidation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Modi%20government%20operates%20mafia%20style%20under%20a%20cloak%20of%20silence%20and%20intimidation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20anyone%20exposes%20its%20modus%20operandi%20of%20corruption%2C%20they%20are%20threatened%20or%20removed.%C2%A0%20The%20latest%20victims%20are%20three%20officers%20of%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%2C%20who%20exposed%20massive%20scams%20in%20government%20schemes%20in%20a%20report%20tabled%20during%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%20of%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1rMgd6hEBh%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1rMgd6hEBh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20operates%20mafia%20style%20under%20a%20cloak%20of%20silence%20and%20intimidation.%20If%20anyone%20exposes%20its%20modus%20operandi%20of%20corruption%2C%20they%20are%20threatened%20or%20removed.%20The%20latest%20victims%20are%20three%20officers%20of%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%2C%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20(%40Jair